        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-01-29T19:47:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-01-29T19:47:00-05:00" n="21"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                <head>21. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d21fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_POL1">POL</gloss> 27 VIET S. Secret; Flash; Limdis.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_GM1">Marshall Green</persName>; cleared by
                            <persName corresp="#p_FMV1">Forrestal</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_MJA1">Mendenhall</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_RD1"
                            >Rusk</persName>, who resumed to the Department of State at 6:25 p.m.;
                        and approved by <persName corresp="#p_HWA1">Harriman</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1964-01-29T19:47:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1964—7:47 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1149. For Ambassador. We have so little info on motivations and other factors
                    involved in current crisis that we leave to your judgment how to handle.
                    Meantime we trust you will make very clear through your actions that we had
                    nothing to do with coup. If you consider it advisable and possible there would
                    seem to us to be merit in preserving <persName corresp="#p_Minh1"
                        >Minh</persName> as head of Government since he appears to have best
                    potentialities for rallying support of people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Ball</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
